medical_history.chief_complaint: Acute symptoms following cesarean section, including hypotension, hypoxemia, tachycardia, dyspnea, cyanosis, and wheezing.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient was admitted for term prelabor rupture of membranes and underwent an emergency cesarean section. Two minutes after the procedure, she developed acute symptoms including hypotension (systolic blood pressure 60-70 mm Hg), hypoxemia (oxygen saturation 60-70%), tachycardia (110-120 beats per minute), dyspnea, and cyanosis of lips and nails.
